--- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com, Zack Widup &lt;w9sz.zack@...&gt; wrote:
&gt;
&gt; I&#39;m not in it to be scared; I&#39;m in it to hopefully learn something. I don&#39;t
&gt; scare easily.
&gt; 
&gt; I have tried for dozens, maybe hundreds of hours to get an EVP recording at
&gt; my home with a regular digital voice recorder. I have never gotten a peep
&gt; there that way. I have also tried in locations that would not be suspect of
&gt; being haunted, like random open country roads and fields. I never got
&gt; anything in those either.  I have gotten many EVP&#39;s in cemeteries and in
&gt; some buildings that were supposedly haunted. This makes me think that this
&gt; method does tap into something that is localized and exists only in small
&gt; areas.
&gt; 
&gt; I guess my house isn&#39;t one of those locations.
&gt; :-(
&gt; 
&gt; I have gotten names on EVP&#39;s a few times and in each case the name could be
&gt; associated with the location from past records (newspapers, hospital
&gt; records, etc.) These were names of real people long dead.
&gt; 
&gt; The radio scanning boxes may tap into a different kind of entity. I don&#39;t
&gt; know. But my experiences indicate that &quot;ghosts&quot; do only inhabit certain
&gt; small areas and they do not go outside those areas.
&gt; 
&gt; Zack
